info.longBusinessSummary: Netflix, Inc. provides entertainment services. It offers TV series, documentaries, feature films, and games across various genres and languages. The company also provides members the ability to receive streaming content through a host of internet-connected devices, including TVs, digital video players, TV set-top boxes, and mobile devices. It has operations in approximately 190 countries. The company was incorporated in 1997 and is headquartered in Los Gatos, California.

content.title: Where Will Netflix Stock Be in 3 Years?
content.summary: Netflix (NASDAQ: NFLX) has been one of the biggest surprises on the stock market in recent years after investors had written off the stock in 2022 following two straight quarters of subscriber losses.  Netflix has added an advertising tier, which has been eagerly embraced by both subscribers and advertisers.  Netflix stock recently topped $1,000 per share for the first time in its history, and its fourth-quarter earnings report shows how these strategies have borne fruit for the leading streamer.

content.title: Nielsen says Christmas had more viewing on streaming services than any day ever
content.summary: Christmas marked a milestone in media history: more streaming than any day ever before, according to the Nielsen company. Netflix streamed two NFL games on that day, with Beyonce appearing as the halftime entertainment when the Houston Texans hosted the Baltimore Ravens. Roughly half of all viewing in the United States that holiday was on streaming services, said Nielsen, the measurement service which has followed the rise of streaming in relation to traditional TV viewing over the past decade.
